title: Tutorial
body:
Hey my human controller! I am Di, warrior in training!

[[Answer:Huh?|Tutorial2]]

title: Tutorial2
body:
Let me walk you through managing my training.

 [[Answer:Continue|Tutorial3]]

title: Tutorial3
body:
Over here is my training actions. Click start on any of them to toggle them on. Be warned however, as I can only currently do 1 at a time.

 [[Answer:Ok|Tutorial4]]

title: Tutorial4
body:
Days is this number over here on the left. Every time it goes up, I gain strength based on the effects of the active actions.

 [[Answer:I see|Tutorial5]]

title: Tutorial5
body:
Over in the middle is the days left until my first fight. Make sure I'm stronger than the enemy by then!

 [[Answer:Okay|Tutorial6]]

title: Tutorial6
body:
My neighbor, Shu from Accounting challenged me to a duel. I have no idea why she would when she's not a warrior, but I never back down from a fight!

 [[Answer:O|Tutorial7]]

title: Tutorial7
body:
Let's become the strongest in this world together!

 [[Answer:Ye|Tutorial8]]

title: Loss0
body: Kuh... You have bested me... bested me with your blade. [[Answer:Loss01|Loss01]]

title: Loss01
body: Right, I figured it wouldn't be too hard to win. Your lack of talent has always betrayed you. [[Answer:Loss02|Loss02]]

title: Loss02
body: But worry not, I have found a capable helper. Our next fight shall not be so easy! [[Answer:Loss03|Loss03]]

title: Loss03
body: Next? What? No, you die here. I can't die so soon so it has to be you. [[Answer:Loss04|Loss04]]

title: Loss04
body: ...Huh? [[Answer:Loss05|Loss05]]

title: Loss05
body: Don't resent me too harshly. [[Answer:Loss06|Loss06]]

title: Loss1
body: This chicken... too much... [[Answer:Loss11|Loss11]]

title: Loss11
body: You were a worthy challenger, but you failed to properly take care of your hunger, and thus you have fallen. [[Answer:Loss12|Loss12]]

title: Loss12
body: Are you going to kill me too? [[Answer:Loss13|Loss13]]

title: Loss13
body: Of course. [[Answer:Loss14|Loss14]]

title: Loss14
body: Why? There's no reason to go this far. [[Answer:Loss15|Loss15]]

title: Loss15
body: You don't know? Then allow me to enlighten you. We must follow the mandate of Heaven's will, delivered to us by the Son of Heaven. To kill as many mortals as we can for a chance to be spared Heaven's wrath. [[Answer:Lose16|Loss16]]

title: Loss16
body: You're telling me that the reason everyone around me is embroiled in war is for such a dumb reason? [[Answer:Lose17|Loss17]]

title: Loss17
body: To go against the will of the heavens is to court death, and I'm not quite ready to pass on. Goodbye, Di. [[Answer:Lose18|Loss18]]

title: Loss2
body: Wait wait wait, stop! [[Answer:Loss21|Loss21]]

title: Loss21
body: Huh? What is it, I have to k-kill you now.[[Answer:Loss21|Loss22]]

title: Loss22
body: But we don't have to! If we just join together, surely we can defy the heavens and survive together![[Answer:Loss21|Loss23]]

title: Loss23
body: No way, there's no way. I'm nowhere near strong enough. Maybe if I was a hundred, no, a thousand times stronger I could have... maybe I... no, there's no point thinking.[[Answer:Loss21|Loss24]]

title: Loss24
body: What if I was a thousand times stronger than I was now? Would you believe I could overthrow the heavens?[[Answer:Loss21|Loss25]]

title: Loss25
body: I-I guess? Not that it matters. We're all weak, and we're all doomed. I'm probably coming after you anyway, so just return to the cycle of reincarnation quietly! [[Answer:Loss26|Loss26]]

title: Loss3
body: Ugh, forget it. Just finish me off already. [[Answer:Loss31|Loss31]]

title: Loss31
body: You seem... oddly calm for someone about to lose their life.[[Answer:Loss31|Loss32]]

title: Loss32
body: What does it matter what I tell you? You'll forget the next time I come here anyway.[[Answer:Loss31|Loss33]]

title: Loss33
body: Next time huh... do you possibly know something greater about this mandate of heaven?[[Answer:Loss31|Loss34]]

title: Loss34
body: I know about as much as you do, but the next time I fight you, I'll cut you down and reach this Son of Heaven. Then maybe there I'll figure out how to split apart the heavens.[[Answer:Loss31|Loss35]]

title: Loss35
body: Your life is still in my hands, but if what you say about having multiple chances is true, then perhaps I can give you a gift to take along the way.[[Answer:Loss31|Loss36]]

title: Loss36
body: Hm, what's that? I can't take any items with me, except these coins for some reason. If you want to give me anything, maybe you can give me more time to train.[[Answer:Loss31|Loss37]]

title: Loss37
body: I can't do that, you may be trying to trick me and escape. No, instead I'll teach you part of my swordsmanship. If you meet me in another life a thousand times stronger, then I'll teach you the whole thing. Until then, goodbye.[[Answer:Loss31|Loss38]]

title: Loss4
body:
Those talismans are pretty tricky, ya gotta teach me how to use them.
 [[Answer:Loss41|Loss41]]

title: Loss41
body:
Enough talk you murderous slime! This is the end for you!
 [[Answer:Loss42|Loss42]]

title: Loss42
body: Ugh, getting your skills are going to be tough huh. Well whatever, its nothing a little strength can't fix. See you next time. [[Answer:Loss43|Loss43]]

title: Loss51
body: And so ends your tale, you upstart mortal. Your efforts to struggle against the flow are futile. Join your fallen comrades in death's embrace. [[Answer:Loss51|Loss52]]

title: Loss52
body: Piece of shit... what even is the point of all this, this mandate, this killing. [[Answer:Loss52|Loss53]]

title: Loss53
body: I merely execute heaven's will. There's no need to question what's beyond you. You lived longer than most ant, and be grateful, for you strength has bought you that time. [[Answer:Loss53|Loss54]]

title: Loss54
body: Unacceptable answer, unacceptable world. I won't stand for this. Next time, next time you will fall. [[Answer:Loss54|Loss55]]

title: Loss55
body: Ha! Good luck with that, killer star. [[Answer:Loss55|Loss56]]

title: Win0
body: You see it right? You have no chance of victory, not even if you train for 100 years. [[Answer:Win11|Win01]]

title: Win01
body: Yeah. I get it. Looks like I'll be the first one on out. Just end things here. [[Answer:Win12|Win02]]

title: Win02
body: No. I won't. I have no intention of letting things continue like this. If the heavens will our deaths, then I will sever the heavens. [[Answer:Win13|Win03]]

title: Win03
body: I would've thought you were full of nonsense, but... To get from your powerless state to heights of strength I can't comprehend... I hope I can put my faith in you, because if you fail, we're bought bound for and eternal suffering worse than death. [[Answer:Win21|Win04]]

title: Win04
body: ...Wait actually? Nice. [[Answer:Win15|Win05]]

title: Win05
body: I'll teach you my skills, use them on your next go at this if this still isn't enough strength to overturn the heavens. [[Answer:Win16|Win06]]

title: Win1
body: Even a thousand hearty meals won't make you strong enough to beat me. [[Answer:Win21|Win11]]

title: Win11
body: I know, but I have no choice. I must fight to live, or be robbed of life. [[Answer:Win21|Win12]]

title: Win12
body: There is another option. Support me with your strength and destroy the heavens. Without the heavenly decree, there's no need for me to kill you. [[Answer:Win21|Win13]]

title: Win13
body: I would have derided anyone else, but if it's someone of your strength... you may just be able to do it. Take my cooking skills and make it to the end for the sake of all mortals. [[Answer:Win21|Win14]]

title: Win21
body: Eek! Please don't kill me, I know you must, but maybe don't. [[Answer:Win31|Win22]]

title: Win22
body: Ok, I won't. [[Answer:Win31|Win23]]

title: Win23
body: I'll give you any- oh wait you will? [[Answer:Win31|Win24]]

title: Win24
body: Yeah. Just give me your bug poison so I can weaken that Son of Heaven and smack him. [[Answer:Win31|Win25]]

title: Win25
body: No more killing? That sounds great to me, I'll help you out in any way you need! [[Answer:Win31|Win26]]

title: Win3
body: I kept my word. I came back a thousand times stronger, and I'm ready to learn your sword. [[Answer:Win31|Win31]]

title: Win31
body: Promise..? Ah, I see, you must have lost to me in the past. If that's the case, then you must truly be the chosen warrior. Take my sword arts and slay the heavens. [[Answer:Win32|Win32]]

title: Win2
body: Your poison didn't even tickle. It's over. [[Answer:Win21|Win21]]

title: Win4
body: Get your slips of paper out of here, I've won, and won by quite a lot. [[Answer:Win41|Win41]]

title: Win41
body: For everyone's sakes, I can't let a powerful being like you exterminate mortal kind?[[Answer:Win41|Win42]]

title: Win42
body: Oh come on, stop yapping at me I haven't even killed anyone (In this timeline at least)[[Answer:Win41|Win43]]

title: Win43
body: Then... are you on the same quest as I, to seal heaven's mandate and restore peace to this Earth?[[Answer:Win41|Win44]]

title: Win44
body: Uh, probably. More importantly, I'm interested in those healing techniques. How about you teach me those so I can bring them with me next time?[[Answer:Win41|Win45]]

title: Win45
body: Of course warrior, my strength is yours.[[Answer:Win41|Win46]]

title: Kill
body: It is done. [[Answer:Kill1|Kill1]]

title: Kill1
body: Indeed it is... by killing me, you'll ensure your karma with heaven is the highest. I'm sure great merit will await you as you are reincarnated.[[Answer:Kill1|Kill2]]

title: Kill2
body: Karma? Whatever, tell me how to cut down the heavens.[[Answer:Kill1|Kill3]]

title: Kill3
body: Hehe... even if you're the strongest mortal, even though you've killed your way through myriads, you're still an ant before the heavens, as am I.[[Answer:Kill1|Kill4]]

title: Kill4
body: Nonsense, I will split the heavens in 2 save everyone's lives! Where is the mandate.[[Answer:Kill1|Kill5]]

title: Kill5
body: Still a foolish mortal to the end. Heaven's will is inherent in all things, the mandate is in your blood, can't you feel it? Soon, very soon, tribulation lightning will incinerate us both and we will be reincarnated as rulers of mortal kind![[Answer:Kill1|Kill6]]

title: Kill6
body: I figured there'd be something like this at the end. Just how strong do I have to be to rend the heavens.[[Answer:Kill1|Kill7]]

title: Kill7
body: A thousand times, a thousand times your strength would be enough but it's too late! Death comes for us both![[Answer:Kill1|Kill8]]

title: Loss5
body: Ugh! Damn it all! [[Answer:Loss51|Loss51]]

title: Win5
body: So? Who's stronger, those heavens of yours or I? [[Answer:Win51|Win51]]

title: Win51
body: How... could this be? This is ludicrous, you can't just become as powerful as the sky above in a matter of days! [[Answer:Win52|Win52]]

title: Win52
body: And yet it has. There's no need for me to kill you, as, if I remember correctly, you're just a pawn of the heavens as well. [[Answer:Win53|Win53]]

title: Win53
body: We-we were supposed to end this world together and perish ourselves! This kind of ending doesn't make any sense! [[Answer:Win54|Win54]]

title: Win54
body: I decide what is sensible and what isn't, and I think these so called heavens are insensible. I think its about time I tore them a visit. [[Answer:Win55|Win55]]
